\b Description:
\b0 \
This is a 3D version of an older project called Addition/Subtraction. It is an attempt to visualize how forces can influence the space around it. There are two competing types of forces in this sim. One is positively charged, the other is negatively charged. They emit particles which move along flow field lines giving a better view as to how the space has been warped.\
\

\b Trivia:
\b0 \
The dark forces create crystal shards at their origin whereas the light forces drip particles onto the floor which quickly evaporate. Why? Why not.\
\

